  "13": {
    "inputs": {
      "text": "**Cinematic Video Script: “The Fall of the Crimson Crown”**\n\n---\n\n**[0:00 - 0:05] — 5-Second Cinematic Sequence**\n\n* **Camera Movement:**  \nFixed tripod mount. Slight, smooth downward tilt (1.5° over 5 seconds) initiated at 0:00, matching the character’s fall. No pan, no zoom, no shake. The tilt begins as her body begins to collapse, ending precisely as her head and right arm strike the stone platform.\n\n* **Scene Composition:**  \nHigh-angle fixed shot, maintaining medium-shallow depth of field. Background remains softly blurred — the male figure in black robes stands immobile, a statue of indifference, framed left. The foreground remains sharply in focus on the woman — her every tear, every trembling breath, every inch of her collapse rendered in hyper-realistic detail.\n\n* **Lighting & Atmosphere:**  \nCold, icy blue ambient light washes the abyssal background, punctuated by faint, floating luminescent particles that drift like spectral dust. A soft, directional top-side light (simulating moonlight or divine residue) cuts through the gloom, isolating her pale, broken form against the darkness. The stone platform in the extreme foreground reflects the light, emphasizing its cold, rough texture.\n\n* **Character Movement & Emotion:**  \nShe begins kneeling, propped on her left elbow, head tilted up in agonized pleading. Her face — tear-stained, red-rimmed eyes wide with despair, crimson floral mark glowing faintly on her forehead, lips smeared with lipstick — stares upward, as if begging the heavens or the distant figure. Her breaths are ragged, her body trembling. As the seconds pass, her strength gives out. She collapses forward — first her torso, then her head, then her right arm — landing with a heavy, muffled *thud* on the stone platform. The silver crown, adorned with red ribbons, hits the stone with a sharp metallic *clang*, followed by the soft, wet *crunch* of her skin and silk against stone.\n\n* **Visual Progression:**  \nAt 0:00 — she’s kneeling, face upward, eyes wide with anguish.  \nAt 0:02 — her body begins to slump, her left hand slipping from the stone.  \nAt 0:03 — her head begins to fall forward, the crown tilting precariously.  \nAt 0:04 — her torso collapses, her right arm flails weakly before hitting the stone.  \nAt 0:05 — her head and right arm lie motionless on the platform. The camera’s downward tilt completes its arc, locking in on her fallen form.\n\n* **Audio Design (Diegetic Only):**  \n- 0:00–0:02: Heavy, breathless weeping and panting — a guttural, choked sob.  \n- 0:02–0:04: The sound of her body collapsing — muffled, wet, and desperate.  \n- 0:04–0:05: A heavy, muffled *thud* as her head and right arm hit the stone.  \n- 0:05: A faint, low-frequency ambient hum — the magical abyss breathing — beneath the silence of her stillness.\n\n* **Final Frame (0:05):**  \nShe lies face-down, the silver crown askew, red ribbons trailing across the stone. Her left hand still grips the edge of the platform, fingers trembling. The male figure in the background remains motionless — a silent, indifferent god. The scene ends in frozen, cinematic stillness — the weight of her despair and the abyss’s indifference holding the frame.\n\n---\n\n**End of Sequence.**\n\n*Note: No BGM, no soundtrack, no dialogue. The silence after the thud is the loudest sound of all.*",
